videos.headline: Louisville wastes little time, strikes for TD on opening drive
videos.description: Louisville takes the opening drive and marches 80 yards in 10 plays resulting with Lamar Jackson finding Jaylen Smith for a five-yard touchdown putting the Cardinals up 7-0 on Duke.

videos.headline: D. Jones pass to T. Rahming for 51 yds for a 1ST down
videos.description: Daniel Jones pass complete to T.J. Rahming for 51 yds to the Lvile 28 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Duke strikes back with nine-yard TD
videos.description: After Louisville scores on the first drive of the game, Duke takes its first possession of the game and finds the end zone when Daniel Jones hits Erich Schneider from nine yards out to tie the game at 7-7.

videos.headline: L. Jackson pass to S. Dawkins for 53 yds for a 1ST down
videos.description: Lamar Jackson pass complete to Seth Dawkins for 53 yds to the Duke 6 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Smith busts loose for huge TD
videos.description: Louisville had been bottled up most of the game until Jeremy Smith breaks through the Duke defense and goes 80 yards to the house putting the Cardinals up 17-7.

videos.headline: Lamar Jackson makes defenders miss for 1st down
videos.description: Lamar Jackson run for 29 yds to the Duke 31 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Duke recovers fumble in red zone
videos.description: Brandon Radcliff run for 10 yds to the Duke 5 Brandon Radcliff fumbled, recovered by Duke Alonzo Saxton II

videos.headline: Duke's Rahming makes great sideline catch
videos.description: Daniel Jones pass complete to T.J. Rahming for 12 yds to the 50 yard line for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Duke claws back capping a 15-play drive with TD pass
videos.description: Duke cuts the Louisville lead to 17-14 with a 15-play drive that takes 8:53 and finishes with Daniel Jones finding Johnathan Lloyd in the end zone from 20 yards out.

videos.headline: Louisville puts game away with Jackson rushing TD
videos.description: After Louisville gets a lifeline on a roughing the kicker penalty, Lamar Jackson makes Duke pay with a two-yard touchdown to put the game away for the Cardinals.
